About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

Welcome to my channel!
I create Mashup, Fan-Made, and Concept Trailers by combining and editing footage from one or multiple movies. These trailers offer a fresh take on existing films, reimagine stories, or even create entirely new movie concepts.
Mashup trailers are a creative way to change the genre, storyline, or focus of a film. For example, a comedy can be transformed into a thriller, or different movies can be combined to create a crossover that doesn‚Äôt exist. These edits allow fans to see their favorite actors and films in a whole new light.
By mixing and re-editing scenes, I aim to build excitement for upcoming releases, highlight unique ideas, and bring cinematic "what-if" scenarios to life. Since these are creative remixes, they may be protected under fair use.

snippet.description:
SURVIVAL STAGE DAY 2 | JULY 30

The 2025 PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP continues with the final day of the Survival Stage in Riyadh! The battle reaches its climax as teams fight for their last chance to reach the Grand Finals and claim their share of the massive $3,000,000 prize pool.

Today is the day‚Äîonly 8 teams will survive and secure the final spots in the Grand Finals. After an intense Group Stage and Day 1 of the Survival Stage, the pressure is at an all-time high. Every moment counts, every zone matters, and only the strongest will advance.

The Survival Stage is where stories are rewritten and underdogs can rise. With limited spots left, this is the moment to BEAT THE HEAT or go home. 

üî•How does SMASH RULE work in Grand Finals? 
After Day 2 of Grand Finals, the Match Point Threshold will be set to the #1 ranked team‚Äôs points +10. Any team that hits this must then win a later match to claim the trophy in the last day of Grand Finals‚Äîwinning the same match where they reach the threshold doesn‚Äôt bring the championship. If no team secures the title via SMASH Rule by Match 18, the team with the highest total points wins under standard rules.

üî• Why You Can‚Äôt Miss 2025 PMWC at EWC:
- The top 16 teams on one stage ‚Äî no second chances!
- Every match counts in the race for the championship!
- Witness PUBG MOBILE history in the making!
- Explosive SMASH RULE format ‚Äî pressure-packed, winner-takes-all action!

snippet.title: Esports World Cup 2025 Day 2 | Can Nihal Sarin reach top 8? | Hindi commentary
snippet.description:
The E-sports world cup 2025 begins on 29th July and goes on until 1st of August 2025. It's a 16-player event with some of the biggest names in the world of chess! 

The commentary will be in Hinglish. Watch on Sony Liv without 7 minutes delay: https://www.sonyliv.com/live-sport/e-sports-world-cup-2025-1790006658/esports-chess-at-ewc-25-day-1-group-stage-29-jul-2025-1090485632?watch=true&utm_source=Share&utm_medium=social_share

Let's try and understand the format:
16 players are segregated in group of 4 players. So there are 4 groups in all. The time control is 10+0. 
On day 1 we had 4 players who topped the 4 groups and will have a rest day on 30th of July 2025.

The players who topped are: 
A group - Levon Aronian
B group - Arjun Erigaisi
C group - Alireza Firouzja
D group - Magnus Carlsen

Now from the losers bracket we will have 4 players who will advance to join these 4 in the top to the Quarter Finals.

A group
1. Nepo vs Artemiev
2. Winner of the above match takes on Esipenko

B group
1. Anish Giri vs Nihal Sarin
2. Winner of the above match takes on MVL

C group
1. Sindarov vs Wei Yi
2. Winner of the above match takes on Nakamura

D group
1. Nodirbek Abdusattorov vs Caruana
2. Winner of the above match takes on Duda

Best of 2 games with a time control of 10+0 followed by Armageddon. At the end of the day we will be left with 8 players in the tournament.

Articles on ChessBase India by Shahid Ahmed:
Day 1: https://chessbase.in/news/Esports-World-Cup-2025-Main-Event-Day-1-report
